items.title: You will now complete a response task.
items.content: The task involves responding two different types of questions, over a number of trials.
For both types of questions, you will start by seeing a screen that looks like this:
Click on the "continue" button to continue.
You will be asked to start each trial by clicking the small button at the bottom of the screen.
Click on the "continue" button to continue.
For the first type of question, you will see a sentence appear on your screen, followed by ‘??TRUE OR FALSE??’.
When you see the ??TRUE OR FALSE?? prompt, your job is to quickly click the answer that best represents your OPINION about whether the sentence you read was true or false.

Let’s try a few practice trials so you can get the hang of it. It’s important to respond as quickly as you can. You will get a warning message if your response is taking longer than the task time limit.
Click on the "continue" button to continue.

content.text: Click the small button below to begin

items.title: Hello, and welcome!
items.content:
This is a demo version of the mousetracking-based Propositional Evaluation Paradigm (MT-PEP). The stimuli used in this demo version are from an experiment relating to placebo effects; however, in principle any stimuli can be used provided they are of a reasonable length (~12 words long maximum).

Note also that the number of trials in the task have been shortened substantially (there are 15 practice trials total and 10 "critical" trials). The whole demo should take less than 5 minutes.

content.text: Click the small button below to begin

items.title: Great!
items.content: Now, for the second type of task, you will also see a sentence appear on your screen, this time followed by either the word ‘TRUE’ or the word ‘FALSE’.

Your job in this task is to IGNORE the sentence itself, and to quickly click the TRUE or FALSE response that corresponds to the word presented below the sentence. If you respond incorrectly, you will see a red X.

Let’s try a few practice trials so you can get the hang of it. Remember, your job is to respond as quickly as you can. You will get a warning message if your response is taking longer than the task time limit. Note: this time, the time limit will be a bit shorter than before, so try to be quick!
Click on the "continue" button to continue.

content.text: You need to click the small button very quickly after you see the sentence.
You will still need to respond to the word, but this trial will not be counted.

You should begin responding as soon as you see the word,
even if you aren't sure how to respond.

items.title: Great!
items.content: You’ve practiced the two different types questions separately, now let’s try a few more practice trials, this time with both types of questions included. We will also increase the speed you need to respond in the trials too.
Click on the "continue" button to continue.

items.title: Thank you!
items.content: That's the end of the demo. If you have questions feel free to contact me at jamie.cummins@ugent.be.

items.title: REMEMBER:

items.content: if you see "??TRUE OR FALSE??", then respond based on whether YOU BELIEVE the sentence is true or not,
if you see "TRUE" or "FALSE", then respond based this word, and ignore the sentence.
Click on the "continue" button to begin the task.
